dspace-development.title: Change DataSpace banner to include more information of disabled submissions

comments.body:
I like Chun's suggestion, and I would build on it a bit. Here's new language I came up with:

"Princeton’s Research Data Repository is becoming the Princeton Data Commons! As we transition, you may not see some of the collections you were once able to submit to in DataSpace, and that means [Princeton Data Commons](https://datacommons.princeton.edu/describe/) is ready for you. For more information, please visit the [Princeton Research Data Service website](https://researchdata.princeton.edu/introducing-princeton-data-commons)."

dspace-development.title: [oar] Task Pool entries are inconsistent between `oartrain` and administrative accounts
[dataspace] Enquire about the large datasets backlog for DataSpace/Globus

comments.body:
There is still a need to make all large (greater than 1 TB) datasets downloadable via Globus.

However, the issue is mitigated by the migration to PDC infrastructure: with everything moving to S3, I expect that it will now at least be possible to download large files via HTTP (whereas it was nearly impossible with DSpace).

What we will want is for large datasets to be migrated one additional step beyond the default, so that they are downloadable via Globus (and the "Download from Globus" button appears on the item page). I consider this part of the overarching migration process, which is still being sorted out.

The highest priority datasets are those currently stored in Dropbox:
- https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp013r074x85b
- https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01b8515r30h
- https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01b5644v47m

figgy.title: Characterization failures should record an error_message on FileSets.

comments.body:
We looked for errors that happen in characterization and found some examples that may be useful in writing tests and updating services. Assuming we just always want to record an error but retry as usual. Here are the errors we found:

- pdf service (`Vips::Error`): https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/100668696
- `CommandFailedError` in tika characterization: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/95345499
- `NoMethodError` in tika characterization: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/96395389
- `NoMethodError` in mediainfo: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/103094817 on this line https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/6bb0c7c9b36e0b5f819164a01f8d487165f973c9/app/characterization_services/mediainfo_characterization_service.rb#L167
- `RSolr::Error::Timeout`: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/97523712
- `DatabaseConnectionError`: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/96017934
- `StaleObjectError`: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/53391/faults/95936844
